The Springboks have a short turnaround from Friday’s comprehensive win over Italy as they take on Canada in Kobe on Tuesday.
Coach Rassie Erasmus has given a few fringe players the opportunity to get some game-time under the belt and all involved will hope they gel reasonably quickly.
There are a few stalwarts on the bench as insurance.
Meanwhile, Canada have only scored 7 points at the tournament to date.
Will it be a horrendously one-sided affair or will there be some competitiveness on offer?
